keyValuePair.Value: So you're out. How disappointed are you?
That must be very frustrating. After winning the first leg, you must have believed you'd progress in the competition. But this defeat puts you out on aggregate. What went wrong for your boys?
I have to take some responsibility.
I have to take some responsibility.

We worked so hard to give ourselves the advantage in the first game. Maybe I should have trusted the boys to go on and get more goals today. Instead, I set us up defensively, to hold onto our lead, and that handed the initiative to our opponents. I'll put my hands up to the mistake.

We worked so hard to give ourselves the advantage in the first game. Maybe I should have trusted the boys to go on and get more goals today. Instead, I set us up defensively, to hold onto our lead, and that handed the initiative to our opponents. I'll put my hands up to the mistake.
There are no excuses.
What can I say? We didn't play well and maybe I should have set us up to be more positive in our approach. But we wanted to defend our lead from the first leg and that plan didn't work out.
We couldn't defend our lead.

I'm very disappointed with our display, of course. We've missed an opportunity today. We had the lead from the first game but we couldn't defend it. The boys are going to have to look at the mistakes they made and learn from them. That just wasn't good enough.
How happy are you to have made it to the next round?
How happy are you to have made it to the next round?
It was close in the end! But despite losing today, you've gone through to the next round on aggregate thanks to your win in the first leg. Are you happy? Or just relieved?
It was close in the end! But despite losing today, you've gone through to the next round on aggregate thanks to your win in the first leg. Are you happy? Or just relieved?
We've got our team spirit to thank.

These were two difficult games but the important thing is we're through. We've got our team spirit to thank, probably. When we went behind today, I feared the worst. But the lads stuck together, showed great composure, and we managed to hang on.
On to the next game now!
Two tight games and we're through thanks to that great performance in the first leg. We have to put this to one side now, though. We have to prepare for the big league match we've got coming up.
It shouldn't have been so close!

I thought we'd done all the hard work in the first game and was pretty confident we'd get to the next round. But we were well off the pace today and that meant it was closer than it should have been. The important thing, though, is we're through!
Are you grateful you're through?

After that great win in the first leg, you must have thought it would be easy enough to get through to the next round. But you lost today and were hanging on at the end. Were your players complacent, do you think?
We just about deserved it, I think.

Over the two legs, I think we were probably the better team. But it was important that we were able to show a bit of resilience today. Once we went behind here, I admit I was worried. But the lads kept their composure and saw us over the line.
We're through. Let's move on now!

That was all more nerve-wracking than it should have been, for sure! Maybe we thought the job was already done. But we've made it into the next round and now all that matters is to prepare properly for our next game.
We looked like we panicked.

Maybe we thought this would be easy after such a good win in the first leg. Definitely our heads weren't right. Once we went behind here, the lads seemed to panic and we were definitely grateful for the final whistle. We know we've got work to do if we want to win things this season.
Despite losing today, you're into the Final. Relieved?
In the end, you're through to the Final thanks to the win in the first leg. What went wrong today? And what lessons will you need to learn if your boys are going to lift the trophy?
We're just happy to be in the Final.

We were up against a good team and I'm just happy we got the goals we needed in the first leg. Maybe the boys were trying a bit too hard to put on a show for our fans today. I'm sure they'll be more effective when it comes to the Final.
Let's just focus on the Final.

Semi-finals are always tense and we never make it easy for ourselves. I was worried when we fell behind here but the lads were resolute enough to get us over the line. The Final will be a very different kind of game.
I think we were nervous today.

Even though we won the first leg, there was plenty of pressure on the players today. They wanted to put on a good display for our fans but, instead, they looked jittery once we went behind. We won't be that poor in the Final, I promise!
You're through to the semis but why was it so difficult today?

You must have thought you were already through after winning the first leg. Instead, this game was very tense and you were hanging on at the end. Do you feel you were a bit lucky to make the semi-finals?
I thought we were the better team.

Over the two games, I think we deserved to go through. I'm very pleased with our strength of character today. When we fell behind, we could easily have panicked. But the boys stuck together, stayed calm, and saw us over the line.
I'm just happy to be into the semis.

The most important thing is that we've made it to the semi-finals. We weren't at our best today but we can put that to one side now. We've an important league game to prepare for and that's all I'm thinking about now.
We looked off the pace today.

Some great attacking play won us the game in the first leg. Maybe the lads thought the job was done. But we never got going today and we paid the price. In the end, we're a little fortunate to have got through to the semi-final.
Was that a pretty professional job?
The challenge was to qualify and you've achieved that. Today's draw sees you through. Were you pleased with the way your team hung onto the lead you had from the first leg?
This is only the start.

I thought we were the better team over the two games. The lads have been very professional in their approach and the senior players have led by example. But they'll know they will be up against better and more dangerous teams now we've qualified.
Let's take one game at a time.

We're through and I'm happy about that, happy about our performances in both legs. But there's no time to dwell on having qualified. We can rest and recover now and then we have to start preparing for our next big game straight away.
The boys are in pretty good form.

I'm very proud of the lads. We set out to qualify and we've achieved that target. It gets more difficult now but I think we've proved we can be competitive at this level. Definitely our attacking play can cause any team problems.

I'm very proud of the lads. We set out to qualify and we've achieved that target. It gets more difficult now but I think we've proved we can be competitive at this level. Definitely our attacking play can cause any team problems.
Two close games but you're into the semis. Can you make the Final?
Two pretty tight games but the draw today puts you into the semi-finals. Were you pleased with the team's performance? Can you make it all the way to the Final now?
We have to be brave.

We have a way of playing and it's seen us into the semi-finals now. The players know that, for us to be successful, they will have to be competitive and brave in every game. If these lads play to their maximum, anything's possible.
We'll wait to find out who we play next.

We've done really well to make the semis after these two legs against excellent opponents. As for getting to the Final, we're in good shape and feel we can give anyone a game. Let's wait and see who we're going to play next.
Our quality can cause anyone problems.

It's great to have reached the semi-final. That's a very good team we've made it past here. The boys are in great form and I think we've got the quality around the team to cause any defence problems. Let's see if we can keep it up and get ourselves through to the Final now.
You're into the Final. Can you lift the trophy now?
It wasn't easy, of course. It took a draw today to get you into the Final. But you're there. What do you expect now? Have your boys got enough about them to go on and lift the trophy?
We've been playing well, I think.

It wasn't a big margin but we definitely deserved to get through to the Final. The lads know they can be even better than they have been in the semis. If they can take the next step, anything's possible for this group of players.
We'll think about that nearer the time.

I'm pleased with how calm and professional we were today. Big games are about fine margins and we kept our heads to get the draw and go through on aggregate. We're happy to be into the Final. We'll start preparing for it nearer the time.
We make ourselves hard to beat.

We've looked so well-organised over these two games. Making ourselves hard to beat is a big reason why we're into the Final. Whoever we face, I'm optimistic because I know I can trust this team to make life difficult for any opponent we face.

We've looked so well-organised over these two games. Making ourselves hard to beat is a big reason why we're into the Final. Whoever we face, I'm optimistic because I know I can trust this team to make life difficult for any opponent we face.
Happy to have made it through today?
That draw today sees you through to the next round. It was a pretty narrow margin in the end but your lads stayed calm and you must be happy with how they've performed?
Let's tighten up defensively.

We were the better team over the two games so well done to the lads. We could have made it easier for ourselves but we had one or two careless moments defensively. The lads know we'll need to stay switched on if we're going to go much further in the competition.
We need to keep our standards high.

Well done to the boys for seeing us through with that draw. But this isn't a time to get carried away. Consistency is everything if we're going to be successful so, for now, all I'm concerned about is getting properly prepared for our next game.
I hope our supporters enjoyed that.

It was a little nervous in the second leg but the draw was enough to see us through. Thanks to our fans for their incredible support. I hope they're enjoying watching the boys make progress in this competition.

It was a little nervous in the second leg but the draw was enough to see us through. Thanks to our fans for their incredible support. I hope they're enjoying watching the boys make progress in this competition.
That defeat is a body blow. How do you explain it?
You must have thought you already had one foot in the semi-finals. Instead, today's defeat means you're out. How can you explain what went wrong?
We just weren't ready for their intensity.

They switched things around, knowing they needed to win. That left my boys outnumbered too often in dangerous areas. We couldn't match their intensity and that put us under pressure almost from kick-off today.
That's a performance we'll try to forget.

There are no excuses. We had given ourselves a great chance of making the semis but today everything went wrong. We have to find the mental strength to deal with this kind of situation if we're going to achieve anything in the future.
We just didn't turn up.

Look, first of all, you have to give credit to the opposition. Even so, it's our own fault we're out. We looked so dangerous in the first leg. I don't know what happened to the lads today, to be honest. We have to be better than that. We just didn't turn up.
How disappointed are you after that display?
After the first leg, it seemed your boys were on their way to the Final. But everything went wrong for you today. How can you explain the difference between the two performances?
They put us under so much pressure.

I think our opponents went into the game with nothing to lose. They played without fear and deserved to win. We couldn't cope with their pace and movement and crumbled under the pressure. I'm devastated. It hurts to miss out on the Final.
Defeat in a semi is difficult to take.

Semi-finals are always tense. We did so well in the first leg but, today, I think the pressure got to my boys. They didn't know whether to go for more goals or hang onto our lead. That gave the opposition their chance.
You have to have the desire.

We were up against a good team but, after our win in the first leg, we should have been able to reach the Final. The lads got out-muscled and out-thought today, though. It was as if we didn't want it enough. It's a devastating defeat.
Why weren't you able to hang onto your lead?
Most people thought you'd be able to hang onto the lead you earned in the first leg but, instead, you were overwhelmed here and you're out. What are your thoughts?
I have to take some responsibility.

I take my share of the blame. Our attacking play was so impressive in the first leg. I should have let the boys go for more goals here but, instead, I went for a more cautious approach. I guess that was what handed to initiative to the opposition today.
We'll look at what happened and learn our lessons.
Of course we're all very disappointed not to qualify. We were so strong in the first leg but we just didn't have the mental toughness to see us through here. I feel sorry for our supporters.
We didn't deserve to go through.

We thought we'd already done the hard work. I was confident we'd go through. But, as soon as went behind here, our confidence crumbled and we made mistake after mistake. Just gave up easy possession all over the pitch. We only have ourselves to blame. We didn't deserve to go through.
How confident are you about the future now?
That was a very impressive display. The job was to qualify but you achieved it in style with wins in both legs. How confident are you now about your prospects in the competition?
It'll be tough from now on.

Well done to the boys. Two good performances. But we're going to have to improve in terms of organisation, I'd say. It's great to qualify but we'll be up against better and more dangerous teams from now on.
Job done. That's all.

Qualifying was our minimum requirement. Well done to the boys on the two wins. But we have a lot of football ahead of us and we want to do well in every competition. Let's just focus on our next game and make sure we're ready.
We definitely looked up for it.
Just at the moment, we really look in the mood every time we play. I'm delighted we've qualified and we've done it comfortably. Getting through these two games is a big step forward for the team.
Just at the moment, we really look in the mood every time we play. I'm delighted we've qualified and we've done it comfortably. Getting through these two games is a big step forward for the team.
You've marched into the Final! Proud of your boys?
That was another comprehensive display. The result hasn't really been in doubt at any stage over the two legs of the semi. Are you running into form just at the right time ahead of the Final?
Let's take another step forward.

It's great to have made the Final. And we've done it in style. I want this to inspire our boys, push them on to be even better. If we're at the top of our game, we know we can beat just about anybody.
We can put the Final to one side now.

It's great to have made the Final. And on the back of two excellent wins. But we need to put that to one side for now. We have an important league game in front of us and we have to focus completely on getting a positive result.
We look a well-balanced team.

Those were two really good team performances. We definitely deserve to be in the Final. We got the balance right in both games. Our defending was solid and that gave us the confidence to push forward and score goals.
Two great performances. Can you make the Final now?
Winning both legs of the quarter final definitely sends out a strong message. I'm sure your boys fear no-one now. How confident are you that the team can go all the way to the Final?
I like our winning mentality.

We were excellent in both games and definitely deserve our place in the semis. But we want to go all the way. I think the lads are growing as a team and developing a winning mentality. That can take us to the Final, whoever we play against next.
There's a long way to go still.

Well done to the boys. Of course I'm happy to reach the semi-final. But we're involved in more than one competition this season. The important thing now is to rest and recover, and then make sure we prepare properly for our next game.
This team can achieve great things.

I'm delighted we've made the semis. I really believe this group of players can go on and achieve great things. Definitely our attacking play is good enough to have every other team worried about coming up against us now.
You're through! How far can this team go now?
There was never much doubt about your team getting through to the next round. Good wins home and away. When you look at your team at the moment, how far do you think they can go?
We'll give anyone a game!

I think something very positive is happening with this group. Certainly, over these two games, I've been very pleased with how the lads are developing as a team: organisation, discipline, spirit. We'll just have to see how far those qualities can take us now.
Let's wait and see.

I'm not thinking beyond the next round. I have to be pleased with how the boys approached both these games. We were positive and aggressive. That's exactly what I want from them. Keep it up and who knows how far we can go?
It'll get tougher now.

I'm very happy for the boys. We were the better side and deserved to go through. I think we realise, though, that we'll be facing better teams from now on and we're going to have to improve if we want to make progress.
